<h2>Description of Collimator-Monochromator System (CMS)</h2>

<p>The collimator-monochromator system was constructed for the HIRDLS
field of view (FOV) and spectral calibration. It consists of an
<b>off-axis parabaloid</b> (clear aperture 280 mm diameter) imaging
either a <b>hot point/structured source</b> contained within the broadband
hot source assembly (BBHSA), or the exit slit of a <b>monochromator</b>. A
flip mirror is used to change the focus of the paraboloid between
these different sources.</p>

<CENTER>
<img src="CMS_fig1.jpg"><BR>
